By Ma Suping, Wang Weikai, and Cui Huiying, southern weekend journalists

Editor in chief | Cao Haidong

After the first batch of patients were admitted to Huoshenshan Hospital for treatment for 4 days, on February 8, the hospital was officially put into use. At 20:00 on the evening of the 8th, the Wuhan Thunder God Mountain Hospital admitted the first batch of transshipment to come to the new coronary pneumonia patient. This is the "new crown pneumonia" after the outbreak, Wuhan in accordance with Beijing "Xiaotangshan" model of a special new hospital, the hospital has a total of 1500 beds, only in-patient, not outpatient.

On the morning of February 8, southern weekend reporters visited the Raytheon Mountain Hospital in Jiangxia District, Wuhan. The two wards have basically been debugged. But according to the construction situation on the spot, the entire Raytheon Mountain Hospital is put into use completely, still needs a period of time.

"The great advantage of the Vulcan and Raytheon hospitals is that they can take in large numbers of patients. By concentrating these patients and cutting off the source of infection, the spread of the disease is reduced. " A military medical university aid Hubei Medical Team chief expert told the southern weekend reporter.

Equipment is final commissioning, two wards will welcome the first batch of patients

1

###Equipment is final commissioning, two wards will welcome the first batch of patients

On the morning of February 8, the Raytheon Mountain Hospital project was in the final stage of construction. Blocks of white clapboard houses are surrounded by vehicles loaded with earthworks and construction materials. PVC pipes are stacked on the roadside. Construction crews are busy with their work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Raytheon Mountain Hospital project has entered the final stage of construction, construction workers are busy outside the board room. (southern weekend reporter, Ma Suping / photo)

On the South side of the hospital, which was once home to athletes for the Games, there were plenty of unoccupied shops on the outside, and behind the north railings were large tracts of white prefabricated buildings under construction.

The 15th and 16th wards of the Department of infection are in the final stage and the first batch of patients will be admitted soon. The first medical team arrived here on February 5. "The ward will be closed at 12 noon, " a doctor in a white lab coat told southern weekend. In the ward, at least a dozen medical staff are shuttling between the ward and the corridor, some checking the signage, some debugging medical equipment.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The exterior scene of 15 wards of one department of Infectious Diseases. (southern weekend reporter, Ma Suping / photo)

Ke Yuhe, who is in charge of medical work in the medical team of Wuhan First Hospital, checks the floor drain in the ward. "because of the deadline, many minor details still need to be adjusted, " he told southern weekend. "The delivery of the ward means that the "outer Shell" has been built, and the medical equipment and computers inside need to be prepared by the medical staff themselves. " Only a paramedic can do a job like setting up a ward.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Leishenshan Hospital Infection 1 Section 15 ward. (Wang Weikai, southern weekend reporter / Photo)

"yesterday afternoon and evening, we moved six or seven trucks just for equipment and medical supplies, " Ke said, adding that only after medical staff had walked through the passages in the ward could they find the problem. A doctor is found in the examination, a ward of the UV light is missing 2 lights. The nurse also found that the door of the buffer room was upside down, which could lead to cross-infection between the doctor and the patient. These minor problems will be corrected during the examination.

On the morning of February 6, Ke was admitted to mount thor hospital. The first batch of medical team altogether 110 people, by Hubei Province Tumor Hospital and Wuhan First Hospital backbone strength composition. Ke Yuhe told southern weekend that some of the medical staff had been infected, and with patients still in the hospital, nearly all of the health care staff have been on duty recently.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The reception center is still under construction. (southern weekend reporter, Ma Suping / photo)

After debugging all the equipment, the 15th and 16th ward of an infection department will receive the first batch of patients. A doctor at Hubei Provincial Cancer Hospital told southern weekend that patients in the first few days would be mostly mild cases, coming from hospitals around the city. Doctors will treat the symptoms according to the COVID-19 for pneumonia (fifth edition) .

Designed to prevent cross-infection, nucleic acid detection can be carried out

2

###Designed to prevent cross-infection, nucleic acid detection can be carried out

The hospital has a total of 1,500 beds, including 2 critical medical wards, 3 sub-critical wards and 27 general wards. Except for the intensive care unit, the wards are all occupied by 2 persons.

Southern weekend reporter noted that there are 53 beds in the 16 wards of the Department of infection. Each ward is equipped with two beds, air-conditioning and television, and a separate bathroom with toilet, water heater, shower and other living facilities.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Each ward is equipped with two beds, air-conditioning and television, and a separate bathroom. (southern weekend reporter, Ma Suping / photo)

As a hospital for infectious diseases, it is extremely important to prevent cross-infection. This concept is also reflected in the design. The floor plan of Raytheon Mountain Hospital shows that each isolation ward is fishbone-shaped, with a medical corridor and a medical work area in the middle and wards on both sides.

"technically, we have adopted the design of three zones and two passages, " Zhang Songmin, deputy chief architect of Zhongnan Architectural Design Institute, explained in an interview with focus. "three zones" means clean zones, semi-polluted zones and polluted zones, "Two channels" refers to the patient channel and the medical care channel.

Southern weekend reporters walked into room 11,12, the front is a mirror, in the middle of the top of the washing table, marked with "hand hygiene" signs, here is the buffer room. Two doors on each side, leading to two separate rooms. The door from the buffer zone to the ward can only be opened for medical treatment and closed for non-treatment time. There's another door from the ward to the patient entrance, patient only.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The health-care corridor in 16 wards of one department is only for the movement of health-care workers. (southern weekend reporter, Ma Suping / photo)

Each headboard has 3 Jacks, equipped with an oxygen supply system, negative pressure suction system. A doctor at the scene explained that the negative pressure suction system is through special devices, so that the air pressure inside the ward is lower than the air pressure outside the ward. This means that all the air that flows from the clean zone to the semi-polluted zone, and from the semi-polluted zone to the polluted zone, does not flow in the opposite direction.

There are also observation windows and transfer windows in each ward. The transfer window acts like a box that can be opened from the outside, where medical staff pass the medicine into the box, where it is sterilized by ultraviolet light and accessed by patients in the room. To avoid infection, the glass on both sides should not be opened at the same time. Observation Window is larger, using transparent material, can not open, medical staff can observe the patient's condition.

Ke Yuhe told southern weekend that the hospital could also test for nucleic acid. NUCLEIC ACID testing is located in the hospital's "heart" medical technology building. The medical technology building will be managed by a number of tertiary level hospitals in Wuhan. It will be equipped with medical and technical units such as electrocardiographic, ultrasound, radiographic and medical laboratory services to meet the diagnostic needs of patients with NCP.

3
Ten thousand people dining room: eat not to speak, lantern festival has dumplings

3

###Ten thousand people dining room: eat not to speak, lantern festival has dumplings

According to the Changjiang daily, 936 construction managers, 7,435 construction workers and 1,491 excavators, cranes and other mechanical equipment were used in the construction of the mountain. On the morning of Feb. 8, cranes, forklifts and hurrying workers filled the construction site.

The 34-year-old Izanghu arrived at the hospital on the third day of the first lunar month after working as a carpenter in Wuhan. Before he was married during the 2008 earthquake in Wenchuan County, he volunteered in Sichuan. This time Wuhan new crown pneumonia epidemic situation is serious, he volunteered to the company to request to Thunder Mountain.

Now, izanghu's two children have been to primary school, often told his father in the phone "pay attention to safety. ". Hubei Hong Lake's family did not like him to come to Thunder Mountain "adventure" , Izanghu hidden family, only told them "the company to recall" , until the family in Wuhan to send a message of peace, the family just know.

The new coronavirus is mainly transmitted by respiratory droplets, and the risk is everywhere where people congregate. Southern weekend reporter noted that the construction site has a dedicated temperature channel workers.

On February 7, "Ten thousand people dining hall" of Raytheon Mountain Hospital swiped friend circle. Before entering the canteen, the workers in the queue must take off their hats for a temperature check. There are no chairs inside the dining hall, several staff members with loudspeakers loop broadcast "line up, eat not allowed to speak, eat immediately left. ". Under unified management, even to the meal point, the temporary canteen also did not appear crowded phenomenon, the atmosphere relative site appears to be quite quiet.

After lunch, some workers sat on the lawn in front of the dining hall. Workers told southern weekend that their workload had recently increased to as much as 7am to 12pm, with one hour off at noon and one hour off in the afternoon.

After dinner, Chen Xiancheng, a native of Ensch, Hubei Province, and several of his fellow workers lay on the lawn and sang folk songs. He was working on the ventilation pipe at the construction site, the first few days on the site, the family was very worried, "but this kind of thing has to be done, if everyone is afraid, can not overcome the epidemic. ".

February 8th is the Lantern Festival. The staff of the third bureau boiled three large pots of glutinous rice balls, which were quickly divided up by the workers. They hope that the dumplings will make workers feel the warmth of the festival.
